# Contributing Guide

Thank you for contributing 🚀

This project uses an automated Pull Request workflow to reduce review noise and ensure consistent quality.

The goal is simple:
👉 Developers own PR readiness  
👉 Automation handles PR state  
👉 Reviewers focus only on code quality  

---

# 🧠 PR Workflow Overview

We use an automated PR state system powered by CI and GitHub Actions.

The workflow is:

1. Open Draft PR
2. CI runs automatically
3. Developer marks PR as Ready for Review
4. Review happens
5. Fixes + Re-review if needed
6. Approval → Auto-merge

---

# 🔁 Detailed Flow

## 1. Open a Draft PR
- Always start with a **Draft PR**
- This indicates work in progress

---

## 2. CI Runs Automatically
CI will:
- build the code
- run tests
- validate checks

### If CI fails:
- Fix the issues
- Push updates
- CI will rerun automatically

👉 Do NOT request review while CI is failing

---

## 3. Mark PR as Ready for Review
Once:
- CI is passing (green)
- Code is complete and self-reviewed

👉 Click **“Ready for review”**

This is an important manual step.

It tells reviewers:
> “This PR is ready to be reviewed”

---

## 4. Review Process
Once marked ready:
- Reviewers will review the code
- They may leave comments or request changes

---

## 5. Address Review Comments
If changes are requested:
- Update the code
- Push changes
- Resolve all comments

---

## 6. Re-request Review
After making changes:

👉 Click **“Re-request review”**

This notifies reviewers that the PR is ready again.

---

## 7. Approval & Merge
Once:
- CI is passing
- No unresolved comments
- Reviewer has approved the PR

👉 The PR will be automatically merged

---

# 🏷 PR Labels (Automated)

These labels are managed automatically by the system:

| Label | Meaning |
|------|--------|
| `needs-ci` | CI failing, PR not ready |
| `changes-requested` | Reviewer feedback pending |
| `ready-for-review` | PR ready for review |
| `approved` | PR ready for auto-merge |

👉 Do not modify labels manually.

---

# 🚫 Developer Responsibilities

As a contributor, you MUST:

- ✅ Open PRs as Draft
- ✅ Ensure CI passes before requesting review
- ✅ Mark PR as “Ready for review” manually
- ✅ Respond to all review comments
- ✅ Mark comments as resolved after fixing
- ✅ Re-request review after changes

---

# ❌ Do NOT

- ❌ Request review before CI passes
- ❌ Leave review comments unresolved
- ❌ Push changes without re-requesting review
- ❌ Try to merge manually when auto-merge is enabled
- ❌ Ignore CI failures

---

# 🧠 Key Principle

> CI validates code correctness  
> Automation manages PR state  
> Developers control readiness  
> Reviewers validate quality  

---

# 🚀 Summary

This system ensures:

- Faster reviews
- Less back-and-forth
- Clear PR states at all times
- No wasted reviewer effort

Thank you for following the process 🙌